reviewText:
This 2 Disc DVD set contains the final 12 episodes from Season 2 of the new Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles TV series. This is DVD release 3 of 3 of the second season episodes. Amazon doesn't always do a good job on their DVD episode listings so here are the episodes that are included in this DVD set:

1. The Manhattan Project
2. Mazes & Mutants
3. The Lonely Mutation of Baxter Stockman
4. Newtralized!
5. The Wrath of Tiger Claw
6. Pizza Face
7. The Legend of the Kuro Kabuto
8. Plan 10
9. Vengeance is Mine
10. A Chinatown Ghost Story
11. Into Dimension X!
12. The Invasion
Disc skipped and froze a lot. Kids were very disappointed
Thumbs up  my son loved it
Fun and action packed dvd for you and the kids.
This iteration of the turtles is gripping, hilarious, and keeps you on the edge of your seat. My husband and I enjoy it just as much as our 6 year old. They just keep getting better!
works good
Very good will use again
Great show.
My grandson loves this video.

Tiger Claw is introduced, Slash returns with the Newtralizer, and New York once again finds itself under attack by the racist and omnipotent Kraang. I'll miss Jason Biggs as Leonardo, however, the rest of the characters and story ended the 2nd season with style!

I bought this video for my boys who are in love with Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles. They weren't really interested in the DVD. I wish I could return it.

My boys love these shows. Nothing to worry about language or anything. Got to keep them from fighting each other and hurting each other when they roll play from the show but it's all it good fun. The story line is pretty good too. I always liked the TMNT movies when I was younger. You can see different things in the epidsodes such as Ho Chin from "Big Trouble Little China" making an appearance. Makes me laugh and even keeps my interest at times.
